### Conclusion

By adopting the Service Layer Pattern, you can create a clean and testable architecture for your CDS system. This approach ensures that business logic is separated from data access and presentation layers, making it easier to manage dependencies, write unit tests, and maintain code quality over time.

This setup also allows for easy integration with additional services or features as the system evolves, ensuring scalability and flexibility in future development phases.

